-- Ecobank of Nigeria Says First-Half Profit Retreats 61% as Revenue Declines
-- Ana Monteiro
-- 2010-07-28T09:25:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/ecobank-of-nigeria-says-first-half-profit-retreats-61-as-revenue-declines.html

          
          
             Ecobank Plc, a Nigerian lender, said
profit for the first half through June dropped 61 percent as
revenue declined.  
 Net income retreated to 1.65 billion naira from 4.25
billion naira, the company said in a statement e-mailed by the
Lagos-based Nigerian Stock Exchange.  
 Revenue dropped to 25.6 billion naira from 30.6 billion
naira, it said.  
          
          


  


        